headline: FDIC asked for crypto ‘pause,’ not debanking, unredacted letters show
summary: Letters released Friday tied to a court case between Coinbase and the FDIC show that the regulator asked banks to pause crypto-related activities, but did not tell banks to stop serving crypto firms.
